WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:28.693 --> 00:32.064
Come on, Hicks.

00:32.097 --> 00:36.235
This is for your
all-time best.

00:40.706 --> 00:42.642
Yay.

00:42.674 --> 00:46.611
I'm the champion,
the champion!

00:46.645 --> 00:48.214
Yes!

00:48.246 --> 00:49.269
Yes!

00:49.270 --> 00:51.483
I gotta call Margaret.

00:51.517 --> 00:53.286
Come on!

01:10.602 --> 01:11.870
Hey, hey, hey.

01:11.903 --> 01:13.206
What's going...
What's going on?

01:13.239 --> 01:14.640
The pressure's
through the roof.

01:14.673 --> 01:16.242
We've got
elevated methane.

01:17.376 --> 01:19.412
We've got to go down
and vent the pumps.

01:30.221 --> 01:31.524
-Give me a boost.
-Yeah, yeah.

01:35.561 --> 01:37.263
Yeow!

01:37.296 --> 01:38.331
Damn.

01:38.332 --> 01:39.365
You okay? You okay?

01:40.498 --> 01:41.867
Empty out the pipes.

01:41.900 --> 01:43.735
Turn off the lights!

01:43.769 --> 01:45.105
<i>The lights!</i>

01:50.808 --> 01:53.646
Damn,
we punctured the crust.

01:53.679 --> 01:55.347
We drilled way too deep!

01:55.381 --> 01:57.250
What is that?

01:57.283 --> 01:58.650
-What is that?
-Look out!

02:01.653 --> 02:03.221
God!

02:03.254 --> 02:06.224
Well, I'd say
I owe you one.

02:06.257 --> 02:07.626
We're going to have to
turn off the valve

02:07.659 --> 02:08.926
on the pressure
relief valve.

02:08.961 --> 02:10.362
Yeah.

02:10.395 --> 02:11.697
Come on!

02:18.804 --> 02:21.608
Holy crap!

02:37.389 --> 02:39.558
Come on, come on,
come on!

02:42.493 --> 02:43.429
Good.

02:43.461 --> 02:44.763
Move it, move it,
move it!

02:44.796 --> 02:45.764
Go!

02:49.935 --> 02:50.937
Come on, move it.

02:50.969 --> 02:52.337
Go! Go!

02:54.473 --> 02:56.409
No!

03:00.712 --> 03:02.715
Forget it, man.
Come on!

03:05.985 --> 03:07.320
Come on!

03:11.556 --> 03:13.692
Don't give up, buddy!

03:13.725 --> 03:15.627
Come on!

04:51.689 --> 04:53.459
<i>No word yet from the USGS,</i>

04:53.492 --> 04:54.927
<i>but we've had three calls
from Long Beach</i>

04:54.959 --> 04:55.995
<i>about a little shake tonight.</i>

04:56.028 --> 04:57.362
<i>Come on, kids.</i>

04:57.396 --> 04:59.398
<i>This is L.A.
Get used to it.</i>

04:59.430 --> 05:00.832
<i>Now back to your daily run</i>

05:00.865 --> 05:02.834
<i>of your favorite
L.A. music.</i>

05:25.990 --> 05:27.125
All right,
now look to your left.

05:27.158 --> 05:28.661
<i>My left or yours?</i>

05:28.694 --> 05:30.062
I don't know
which way you're facing!

05:30.095 --> 05:30.996
<i>I don't see anything.</i>

05:32.598 --> 05:34.467
<i>I don't see
any camping stuff.</i>

05:34.500 --> 05:36.769
It's, it's behind the box
marked Christmas.

05:36.802 --> 05:38.804
-There's Christmas stuff, behind it.
-Hello.

05:38.836 --> 05:41.940
Hey. I thought you weren't picking
her up until later this evening.

05:41.973 --> 05:44.476
I just wanted to see if she wanted
to hang out with the old man.

05:44.509 --> 05:45.644
<i>Mom, I don't see any...
Okay.</i>

05:45.677 --> 05:47.112
<i>-I found it.
-Okay, good.</i>

05:47.146 --> 05:48.646
<i>-What's she looking for?
-Heads up!</i>

05:48.680 --> 05:50.449
Wait! Going camping?

05:50.482 --> 05:53.052
<i>Me, with Cindy. Crap.
She's gonna be here any minute.</i>

05:53.084 --> 05:55.987
Hey, I thought
we had plans for tonight.

05:56.021 --> 05:58.591
Do you really think Pizza and
Redbox qualifies as plans?

05:58.624 --> 06:00.893
<i>Sorry, Dad. We'll do something
next week, okay?</i>

06:00.925 --> 06:02.394
No, no, it's not okay.

06:02.427 --> 06:03.596
You can't just, you know,

06:03.629 --> 06:05.097
cancel on someone
at the last minute.

06:05.129 --> 06:06.432
Really?

06:06.464 --> 06:07.866
Hey, just tell
Cindy's parents

06:07.899 --> 06:09.534
that you've made a commitment
and that we are...

06:09.567 --> 06:10.969
<i>Her parents aren't going!</i>

06:11.002 --> 06:12.137
<i>Ma, I can't find the tent.</i>

06:12.170 --> 06:14.639
Well, it's up there...
somewhere.

06:14.673 --> 06:16.975
Wait. Hang on a second. There's no
chaperone, did you know about this?

06:17.009 --> 06:19.645
What do you want her to do? Sit around and
pray that you don't stand her up again?

06:19.677 --> 06:21.713
She's got her own life,
you know.

06:21.747 --> 06:24.516
Yeah and I would appreciate not
being cut out of it completely.

06:24.550 --> 06:27.186
It's three days in a national park.
They'll be fine.

06:27.218 --> 06:29.154
Hey, you want to go camping?
Hey, that's great.

06:29.187 --> 06:30.555
You know,
I'm going to be up there.

06:30.588 --> 06:31.757
I'm breaking ground
at Station Five.

06:31.790 --> 06:33.559
You can hang out
with your old man.

06:33.591 --> 06:34.692
<i>Pass.</i>

06:34.726 --> 06:37.195
Look, it is dangerous up there
in the woods, you know.

06:37.228 --> 06:40.532
What would you do
if you ran into bears?

06:40.565 --> 06:42.133
<i>Never sleep in their beds,</i>

06:42.166 --> 06:44.502
<i>sit in their chairs,
or eat their porridge.</i>

06:44.536 --> 06:47.139
Look, I'm not
comfortable with this.

06:47.172 --> 06:48.741
Two girls alone
in the woods...

06:48.774 --> 06:50.942
<i>Derrick and his friends
will be there.</i>

06:50.975 --> 06:54.512
Hang on. There's boys?
That is worse than bears.

06:54.545 --> 06:55.647
You, you knew about this?

06:55.680 --> 06:56.981
Dad!

06:57.014 --> 06:58.550
You have to trust me.

06:58.584 --> 07:01.153
You know I can
take care of myself.

07:01.185 --> 07:03.788
Okay.

07:03.822 --> 07:04.956
Thanks, Dad.

07:06.959 --> 07:08.526
Just promise me...

07:08.560 --> 07:10.495
If you run into your grandmother
wearing a nightie,

07:10.528 --> 07:13.798
just double check...
Might be a wolf.

07:13.831 --> 07:14.966
Sure thing, Dad.

07:15.000 --> 07:17.101
Plus, grandma's way furrier,

07:17.134 --> 07:18.570
and she has thumbs!

07:20.572 --> 07:22.442
All right.
Do you have your checklist?

07:38.189 --> 07:40.225
Could be nothing.

07:40.259 --> 07:42.028
Probably nothing.

07:44.829 --> 07:45.865
Okay.

07:53.939 --> 07:56.775
And now it's something.

08:07.586 --> 08:09.855
Dr. Gladstone,
a delightful surprise.

08:09.887 --> 08:12.024
How many calls
have we had this morning?

08:12.057 --> 08:14.727
Just eight.

08:14.759 --> 08:16.661
No, I haven't seen
last night's seismographs.

08:16.694 --> 08:18.029
I haven't even had
a cup of cof...

08:18.062 --> 08:19.697
God!

08:19.730 --> 08:23.302
Doc,
it's my first day.

08:23.334 --> 08:25.169
Can't we just...

08:25.202 --> 08:27.005
The L.A. basin
always shows signs

08:27.038 --> 08:29.307
of deep crust activity
when...

08:29.341 --> 08:33.678
Intensifying aftershocks?
Pre-shocks?

08:33.711 --> 08:35.246
Don't you think
that's a little farfetched?

08:35.279 --> 08:37.315
Okay, I'll...
I'll look into it.

08:37.349 --> 08:39.083
Doc, I'll look into it.

08:39.116 --> 08:40.051
I promise.

08:53.130 --> 08:54.732
Drunk as could be.

08:54.765 --> 08:56.735
Looks the broad
right in the face and says,

08:56.768 --> 08:57.870
"If that's not a banana,

08:57.903 --> 08:59.904
What's it doing
in my cornflakes?"

09:01.606 --> 09:02.875
Who wants more champagne?

09:04.308 --> 09:05.810
We're out!

09:19.191 --> 09:21.726
Don't start without me!

09:25.163 --> 09:26.365
I've got the bubbles.

09:26.398 --> 09:28.801
Who's ready
for the...?

09:34.740 --> 09:36.240
<i>-Nice car.
-Thanks.</i>

09:36.274 --> 09:39.845
You,
you checked the fluids?

09:39.878 --> 09:41.146
Yep, changed the oil
this week.

09:43.280 --> 09:46.284
What about these? When's the
last time you had them rotated?

09:46.317 --> 09:48.252
I think
three months ago.

09:48.285 --> 09:49.988
You think,
or you know?

09:50.022 --> 09:50.890
I know.

09:50.923 --> 09:52.825
The receipts are in
the glove compartment.

09:55.092 --> 09:56.260
What's in the cooler?

09:56.293 --> 09:58.963
Just food and soda, sir.

09:58.996 --> 10:00.198
Better be!

10:02.868 --> 10:03.736
Hey.

10:03.769 --> 10:06.304
Damn, Nicki.
Your dad is way protective.

10:06.337 --> 10:09.073
Well, this weekend
he might have a reason to be.

10:10.942 --> 10:12.677
-What, what are you planning?
-Nothing!

10:12.711 --> 10:13.762
Mind your business.

10:13.763 --> 10:14.812
Is it something dangerous?

10:14.846 --> 10:16.932
My God!

10:16.933 --> 10:19.018
If, if it is, then we should
all be informed of it.

10:19.051 --> 10:20.152
Do you have firearms?

10:20.184 --> 10:21.819
-No.
-Of course not!

10:21.852 --> 10:23.855
Fireworks? They can be lethal...
Especially in the forest.

10:23.889 --> 10:25.658
You know, Southern California
has very dry summers.

10:25.691 --> 10:27.926
Shut it, Toblosky,
or we're leaving you behind.

10:27.958 --> 10:30.261
You better not be blabbing the
whole way or so help me, God,

10:30.294 --> 10:32.264
I will just dump your ass
in the middle of the desert,

10:32.297 --> 10:33.766
and I don't care
if you're paying for gas.

10:33.798 --> 10:35.167
-I'm not putting up with it.
-Okay, Warner.

10:35.200 --> 10:36.835
God!

10:36.868 --> 10:37.970
-Jeez!
-This is ridiculous!

10:38.003 --> 10:39.738
Your dad is a mammoth
pain in the ass.

10:39.770 --> 10:42.240
What is he like...
A Scottish Mountie or something?

10:42.274 --> 10:44.409
He's an engineer
for a fracking company.

10:44.442 --> 10:46.077
What the frack is fracking?

10:46.110 --> 10:48.146
It's actually very cool...
And very controversial.

10:48.179 --> 10:49.747
You know,
what they do is they...

10:49.780 --> 10:52.083
They drill like a mile down
into the earth's crust

10:52.116 --> 10:54.687
looking for, you know,
natural gases and oil.

10:54.720 --> 10:56.788
Then when they find it,
they drill sideways

10:56.822 --> 10:58.423
and let off
a series of explosions

10:58.456 --> 10:59.891
and finally
they force it out

10:59.924 --> 11:03.327
with millions of gallons
of pressurized water.

11:03.360 --> 11:05.297
What did I just say?

11:05.330 --> 11:06.732
Well, we're not driving!

11:06.764 --> 11:08.399
<i>Okay. Calm down.</i>

11:08.432 --> 11:10.068
Jeez, Warner.

11:12.971 --> 11:14.306
Ok, I think
we're ready to go.

11:14.339 --> 11:15.307
Awesome!

11:15.340 --> 11:17.776
Hey...
Okay.

11:17.808 --> 11:20.778
I will be right up there
if you want to see the rig...

11:20.812 --> 11:24.450
7 p.m.-that's when
we're turning all the pumps on.

11:24.482 --> 11:25.783
It's going to be
quite a sight.

11:25.817 --> 11:27.418
Yeah, we'll be sure
to stop by.

11:27.451 --> 11:29.053
Can we please go now?

11:29.086 --> 11:30.923
One last question...

11:30.956 --> 11:33.125
How many beers before
it's no longer safe to drive?

11:33.158 --> 11:35.060
Dad! Derrick,
don't answer that question.

11:35.092 --> 11:36.394
<i>Well, actually
it's the blood alcohol...</i>

11:36.427 --> 11:39.097
Hey, I'm asking him,
not you.

11:39.130 --> 11:40.365
Come on, tough guy.

11:40.398 --> 11:41.466
-Nothing.
-One beer.

11:41.500 --> 11:43.168
No.
Wrong!

11:43.201 --> 11:44.436
You're under 21.

11:44.469 --> 11:45.804
That's it, young lady.
Out of the car!

11:45.836 --> 11:47.272
Come on. No.

11:47.273 --> 11:48.707
Dad, stop it!

11:53.845 --> 11:55.413
All right. You just...

11:55.447 --> 11:59.083
You call me if there's
any problems, okay?

11:59.116 --> 12:00.284
No trouble, you hear?

12:00.317 --> 12:01.385
Yes, sir.

12:01.418 --> 12:02.954
<i>Thanks, Dad.</i>

12:02.988 --> 12:05.324
Bye.

12:07.125 --> 12:08.094
Sorry.

12:11.529 --> 12:12.964
Too possessive Jack.
You keep it up,

12:12.998 --> 12:15.100
you're going to
push her away even more.

12:15.133 --> 12:18.537
It's just the dysfunctional stuff.
Am I too involved or not enough?

12:18.570 --> 12:22.975
Being overprotective isn't
the same as being supportive.

12:23.008 --> 12:25.043
You've got to start
trusting her.

12:25.076 --> 12:27.946
What about that GPS tracking
app that you put in her cell?

12:27.979 --> 12:29.314
Yeah, but that's different.

12:29.346 --> 12:30.348
Really?

12:30.381 --> 12:32.116
Yeah.

12:32.149 --> 12:33.251
Hey, yeah.

12:33.284 --> 12:34.852
Hey, boss. Yeah.

12:34.885 --> 12:36.855
I'm I'm running
a little bit late.

12:36.888 --> 12:40.057
I've just got to pick up Hector
and I'll be on my way.

12:40.091 --> 12:41.793
Before you head there,
I need you to stop by

12:41.826 --> 12:43.261
Pump Station Three.

12:43.294 --> 12:44.529
We've got a little spike,

12:44.562 --> 12:46.298
<i>then the station went dead.</i>

12:46.331 --> 12:47.566
<i>We lost all our readings.</i>

12:47.599 --> 12:49.268
Come on, move it!
Let's go!

12:49.301 --> 12:50.502
<i>Come on, move it!</i>

12:50.534 --> 12:52.937
Okay, yeah,
wha-what about Paxton?

12:52.971 --> 12:54.405
<i>Yeah, I haven't heard back.</i>

12:54.438 --> 12:57.408
He pulled an all-nighter
so he's probably crashed out.

12:57.442 --> 12:59.010
<i>What is your problem?</i>

12:59.043 --> 13:01.245
Today, please!
Today!

13:01.278 --> 13:02.581
Yeah, and security?

13:02.614 --> 13:04.583
<i>That drunk is probably
passed out, too.</i>

13:04.615 --> 13:06.585
<i>He's as big of an idiot
as this moron</i>

13:06.618 --> 13:08.086
in front of me.

13:08.119 --> 13:09.288
Move it, toots!

13:10.621 --> 13:13.057
It's not like Paxton
not to check in, though.

13:13.091 --> 13:15.894
This is L.A., 55 means 70.

13:15.927 --> 13:17.329
Pick it up, Grandma!

13:19.230 --> 13:21.033
Ho, nice!

13:28.306 --> 13:30.375
Hey, Jack, I'll see you
this afternoon.

13:30.408 --> 13:31.610
It's a big day, man.

13:31.643 --> 13:34.046
I can't wait
'til we turn on...

13:34.078 --> 13:36.948
Would you
look at this guy?

13:36.981 --> 13:38.583
Stay in your lane, idiot!

13:40.585 --> 13:42.187
Listen, I've,
I've got to go.

13:42.220 --> 13:43.488
Sounds like it's going to be
one of those days.

13:43.520 --> 13:45.089
Sorry.

13:45.123 --> 13:50.028
Yeah, sorry to pile it on,
but could you just sign this

13:50.061 --> 13:52.398
and mail it in
whenever you can?

13:54.399 --> 13:55.900
Sure.

14:01.105 --> 14:02.206
Hello?

14:02.240 --> 14:04.876
Hi. I'm looking
for Dr. Booker.

14:04.909 --> 14:08.145
Could you, point me
in the right direction?

14:08.178 --> 14:10.348
Hello?

14:10.381 --> 14:13.251
Hello?
Mi-Miss?

14:13.284 --> 14:14.352
Hi there.

14:14.385 --> 14:15.353
Dr. Schiffman.

14:16.520 --> 14:18.222
Not Dr. Schiffman.

14:18.255 --> 14:20.424
Yes. It's the second time
I've been called doctor today.

14:20.457 --> 14:22.394
I'm not quite used to it.

14:22.427 --> 14:23.512
Emily's fine, sir.

14:23.513 --> 14:24.596
Michael.

14:24.629 --> 14:26.298
I will show you
around here.

14:26.331 --> 14:27.499
Am I early?

14:27.532 --> 14:29.100
What time does
everyone show up?

14:29.134 --> 14:31.637
I'm afraid this is it.
Budget cuts, you know?

14:31.669 --> 14:33.437
I'm actually a little surprised
they hired you,

14:33.471 --> 14:36.674
although I can use the company
and the help, especially today.

14:36.707 --> 14:39.144
This has been
a very funny morning.

14:39.177 --> 14:41.013
We've had 15 reports
since last night

14:41.046 --> 14:42.514
and I can't make
a lick of sense of it.

14:42.547 --> 14:44.582
So I've heard.

14:44.615 --> 14:45.616
Gladstone.

14:45.649 --> 14:47.084
Yeah.
I met him last year

14:47.118 --> 14:48.987
at a paleo-earthquake
seminar at Berkley

14:49.019 --> 14:51.155
and somehow I became
his new best friend.

14:51.188 --> 14:53.024
Yeah, that guy...
He's like a mutt...

14:53.057 --> 14:54.326
You pet him once,
he never leaves your lap.

14:54.359 --> 14:56.528
He heard my thesis
and he had to meet me!

14:56.561 --> 14:58.663
<i>Yes, I read that thesis.</i>

14:58.697 --> 15:00.365
It was on containment...

15:00.398 --> 15:01.500
-Epicenter.
-Yeah.

15:01.533 --> 15:03.032
Epicenter containment, yeah.

15:03.033 --> 15:04.468
-Yeah, it was quite...
-Ridiculous?

15:04.501 --> 15:05.569
No, I wasn't
going to say that.

15:05.602 --> 15:07.072
No, it's okay,

15:07.105 --> 15:08.507
my, my professors
thought the same thing.

15:08.539 --> 15:11.575
However, that ingenious theory
did earn me a strong C minus.

15:11.609 --> 15:14.480
And a job
at the glorious USGS.

15:16.480 --> 15:18.716
Yeah, you know,
you would think the state

15:18.750 --> 15:20.952
would make this place
more of a priority.

15:20.985 --> 15:23.322
Well, I do have a 24-hour
hotline to the governor

15:23.355 --> 15:24.389
anytime I need it.

15:24.422 --> 15:26.158
Really?
What's he like?

15:26.191 --> 15:28.560
I've never met him, so...

15:28.592 --> 15:32.496
Also, there is the sign-up sheet
for the company softball league.

15:32.529 --> 15:35.433
So far it's just me.

15:35.466 --> 15:37.269
I play first base.

15:37.302 --> 15:39.204
-Okay.
-Yeah.

15:39.236 --> 15:42.307
Here's the rules for using
the kitchen microwave,

15:42.340 --> 15:43.575
dah-dah, dah, dah.

15:43.607 --> 15:46.644
And over here
is your workstation.

15:46.677 --> 15:49.480
Now, we have been getting
calls all morning

15:49.514 --> 15:51.048
about tremor activity, okay?

15:51.081 --> 15:53.317
Nothing major,
no major damage...

15:53.350 --> 15:55.586
Just broken glass,
things flying off the shelves.

15:55.620 --> 15:57.489
The thing is,
the major scales...

15:57.522 --> 16:00.057
They haven't registered anything
above a semi passing by.

16:00.091 --> 16:01.360
Okay,
so what can I do?

16:01.393 --> 16:04.997
Well, we have 300 sensors
in the L.A. river basin.

16:05.029 --> 16:07.031
These reports are from
the last 12 hours.

16:07.065 --> 16:08.166
I'm gonna need you
to look through there,

16:08.198 --> 16:10.334
see if there's
any unusual peaks.

16:11.201 --> 16:13.437
Is this some sort of
new-guy hazing?

16:13.471 --> 16:15.240
Don't you have some intern

16:15.273 --> 16:19.110
or a computer
equipped to do this?

16:19.144 --> 16:21.679
We barely have enough money
for staples for this stapler.

16:23.514 --> 16:25.049
I shouldn't
have used that one.

16:25.082 --> 16:27.552
Sorry, kid.
Just you and me, honey.

17:16.300 --> 17:17.269
Dude!

17:31.316 --> 17:33.052
Dude?

17:37.721 --> 17:38.823
<i>Nate down in Palms.</i>

17:38.856 --> 17:40.692
<i>Callers told us a big sinkhole
just opened up</i>

17:40.724 --> 17:41.826
